      "text": "Energy consumption, water and land use, greenhouse gas emissions, ocean acidification, tropical forest loss, species extinction: We would not have made the transition from a growth-oriented economic model motivated by greed, envy and the desire for dominance to a functioning sufficiency economy, that is, to a truly sustainable and decelerated form of economic activity.\n"
    },
