      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ff49c4ef59bb5c16",
      "text": "When it comes to the climate catastrophe, it is no longer intellectually honest to be optimistic. Mankind has been \"lying to itself\" for too long. Metzinger pleads for a new culture of consciousness, without God and without religion, for a new, secular spirituality, also by means of meditation, for an attitude of mind that links Western science with Eastern meditation practices.\nHow should this be shaped? Why do theologies, religions, faith communities have no probity and no persuasive power? And how will the new culture of consciousness be able to save humanity and the planet?\nA conversation led by [[Ahmad Milad Karimi]].\n\n"
