        "text": "Within the next two centuries, [[Thomas Metzinger]] expects the \"global panic point\", i.e. the realization that catastrophe will befall mankind. Energy consumption, water and land use, greenhouse gas emissions, ocean acidification, tropical forest loss, species extinction: We would not have made the transition from a growth-oriented economic model motivated by greed, envy and the desire for dominance to a functioning sufficiency economy, that is, to a truly sustainable and decelerated form of economic activity.\nWhen it comes to the climate catastrophe, it is no longer intellectually honest to be optimistic. Mankind has been \"lying to itself\" for too long. Metzinger pleads for a new culture of consciousness, without God and without religion, for a new, secular spirituality, also by means of meditation, for an attitude of mind that links Western science with Eastern meditation practices.\nHow should this be shaped? Why do theologies, religions, faith communities have no probity and no persuasive power? And how will the new culture of consciousness be able to save humanity and the planet?\nA conversation led by [[Ahmad Milad Karimi]].\n\n"
